help:
Overview

Help message can have as plain text so images and videos.

 

For images it is recommended  do not use external sources but inset images into content. To that that, please open image and copy it into clipboard, then paste into editor.

 

It is not allowed to use MS Office files in help, but you can convert it to PDF and use it.

 

It is allowed to use external video and PDF (media). External media should be available to all users and to PVR application itself. It can be some shared folder, youtube, or other streaming service or Sharepoint/OneDrive

 

Using Sharepoint/OneDrive to store media files

 

1. Upload video or PDF file to shrepoint/onedrive folder

2. Define access rights to this file so all PVR users can view this file

3. Open file (click on file name)

4. Click on “...”->”Embed”

5. “Copy Embed Code”

 

6. In PVR on “Edit Help Message” page,click on “Insert”->”Media”->”Embed” tab

Paste code and press “ok” Button

7. Click “Ok” - video or PDF will be inserted.

8. Watching  video or pdf is not available in edit mode. To watch it, please save help message and click “view” on list page.

 

 

You can also use any other streaming services with “embed” support. For Example to use YouTube you should open required video on YouTube site, then click “Share”->”Embed”, then copy code from modal. Insert code into help editor (see step 6 above).

 

Export/Import

 

 You can export all help messages bu press “export” button on listing page. To import content, please select json file with data and press “Import” Button

 

If importing content has references for media in some Sharepoint, then you need to

1. copy files to some folder in your SharePoint,

2. Grant access to this files to all PVR users

3. Update References (select this folder in Sharepoint and press “Update References To Media”
